Lagos – The Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria (FAAN) said it would on Saturday shut down the D Wing of Murtala Muhammed International Airport (MMIA), Lagos for routine maintenance. A statement by Mrs. Henrietta Yakubu, the General Manager, Corporate Communications, FAAN said that the aspect of the terminal would be shut for two hours between the hours of 10am and noon. Yakubu noted that all flight operations at the wing would be diverted to E Wing within the period, while the maintenance work would last. She urged the travelling public, airlines and other users of airport to bear with the airport manager during the temporary closure stressing that FAAN was committed to its core values of safety, security and comfort.